
[1]expensive

   EXPENS'IVE, a. Costly; requiring much expense; as an expensive dress or
   equipment; an expensive family. Vices are usually more expensive than
   virtues.

   1. Given to expense; free in the use of money; extravagant; lavish;
   applied to persons. Of men, some are frugal and industrious; others,
   idle land expensive.

   2. Liberal; generous in the distribution of property.

   This requires an active, expensive, indefatigable goodness.
